---
title: About
description: Normal person stuck in a computer.
---

{% extends 'layouts/base.njk' %}

{% block content %}
  <div class="wrapper">
    <main id="main" class="flow">
      <header>
        <div class="container u-text--center">
          <h1>{{ title }}</h1>
        </div>
      </header>
      <section class="aboutMe flow u-truncate u-truncate--center">
        {% renderFile './src/_includes/partials/bio.md' %}
        <p>My social media presence is sparse, but you can find me at the following locations:</p>
        <ul>
          {% for social in metadata.socials %}
            <li><a href="{{ social.url }}">{{ social.name }}</a></li>
          {% endfor %}
        </ul>
        <p>Did I mention I'm something of an amateur graphic designer? Evidenced by the following picture of me and my family of Mark
          Zuckerbergs.</p>
        <figure class="zuckerbergs">
          <img
            src="{{ metadata.cloudinary }}/c_scale,f_auto,q_auto:eco,w_800/v1646349104/blog/The_Whole_Gang_i16cp7.webp"
            alt="A photoshopped image of me and my family in Alaska, but with Mark Zuckerberg's face on everyone except for me."
            decoding="async"
            width="800"
            height="531"
            id="me"
          />
          <figcaption>This picture got me over a thousand likes on a <a href="https://clickhole.com/">ClickHole</a> Facebook post, so I'd
            say it's one of my greatest
            achievements right behind that time I won a guitar by placing first in a Guitar Hero contest.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </section>
    </main>
  </div>
{% endblock %}

{% block style %}
  {{ super() }}
  <style>
    .quickLinks ol {
      padding: 0;
    }

    .zuckerbergs {
      margin-block: 3rem;
      max-inline-size: 45rem;
    }

    .zuckerbergs figcaption {
      margin-block-start: .5rem;
    }
  </style>
{% endblock %}
